// This paper connects the abstract K-Q framework (Volume IX) to the modern
// program of Picard-Lefschetz path integrals and resurgent asymptotics.
// The Feynman path integral, treated as a K operator, decomposes into
// Lefschetz thimbles — each a distinct K-representation yielding the same
// observable under Q. Resurgent relations between saddle sectors are shown
// to be instances of Q∘K composition on ker(Q): perturbative series
